  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH Response to Rain Flood 2020 Affected Population of  District Mirpurkhas - Sindh, Pakistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to address the WASH immediate needs of the 8,750 households (61,250 persons) rain flood affected families of two UCs i.e. Mir Khuda Bux and Soofan Shah of Tehsil Dighri, District Mirpurkhas Sindh Pakistan. 

Project will address the WASH needs of unorganized roadside camps where affected populations are still living and serve in villages where early recovery and rehabilitation process is yet to start.    

The major activities of project which includes provision of safe drinking water by tankers to 61,250 affected  as well as provision of aqua tabs, non-food items i.e. mosquito net, hygiene items, jerry cans and tarpaulins sheet as well as provision of temporary latrines (Raised Structure), along with hygiene awareness including the handwashing and social distancing for COVID preventions. 

This project&#x2019;s relief operations will be executed by Advocacy Research Training and Services (ARTS) Foundation, which is already working in the targeted areas since 2008.</narrative>
  </description>
